    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "The Cultural Heritage Preservation Group will be following the traditional practice and using traditional materials to bring the temple back to its original size and shape.  As no drawings exist the reproduction of the temple will be made as authentic as possible based on the surviving historical photos, water color sketches and the original components of the temple. The reconstruction design of the temple will be based on the existing base in stone which will provide the ground floor plan with exact locations of the 20 timber columns. The rebuilding will take place on the intact foundation and stepped platforms, using some of the original struts as well as the original bronze finial."
      },
      "ne": null
